Q. Favourite thing about The Space? 
A. The dedication to supporting new theatre makers. It‚Äôs how I first came to The Space many years ago. I never left. Even during lockdown new writing is being commissioned. & funding flows straight to the theatre makers, directors & performers

Q. Describe your lockdown in 1 word
A. Internet

‚ö°Ô∏è
Q. What are you going to take from this lockdown experience? 
A. I‚Äôve been playing, reading, writing & watching so much theatre. Now more than ever I‚Äôve realised we NEED it. I‚Äôve seen incredible generosity around me. I'm taking knowledge, skills & kindness from this lockdown

Q. Space highlight pre lockdown?
A. The twice yearly Bloom Festival at the Canary Wharf Crossrail Roofgarden! I loved hosting it. We had so many lovely performers. And there were lots of balloon sword fights.

Q. Space highlight during lockdown?
A. The Space Theatre Club of course! For me it consists of three main things that give me joy; the theatre we watch, the people who come, and the guests who join us.

Q. Lockdown shout out. 
A. These months I have been dividing my time (so much free time) between The Space & @escapeintime. Together with a bunch of creatives I‚Äôve been devising a new adventure which will open soon on the C16th ship the Golden Hind in the Thames nr London Bridge.
